        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Right Shifts</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The result of a right shift of a negative-value signed integral type</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Shifting a negative value to the right yields half the absolute value, rounded down.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example, a signed <ph id="ph1">`short`</ph> value of –253 (hex 0xFF03, binary 11111111 00000011) shifted right one bit produces –127 (hex 0xFF81, binary 11111111 10000001).</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>A positive 253 shifted right produces +126.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Right shifts preserve the sign bit of signed integral types.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>When a signed integer shifts right, the most-significant bit remains set.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example, if 0xF0000000 is a signed <ph id="ph1">`int`</ph>, a right shift produces 0xF8000000.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Shifting a negative <ph id="ph1">`int`</ph> right 32 times produces 0xFFFFFFFF.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>When an unsigned integer shifts right, the most-significant bit is cleared.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example, if 0xF000 is unsigned, the result is 0x7800.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Shifting an <ph id="ph1">`unsigned`</ph> or positive <ph id="ph2">`int`</ph> right 32 times produces 0x00000000.</source>
        </trans-unit>
